-- MOVES-Oaktree appoints ex-AIG executive as CEO
-- 
-- Mon Oct 06, 2014 10:31AM EDT
-- None



Oct 6 (Reuters) - Credit investment and private equity firm Oaktree Capital Group LLC <OAK.N> appointed Jay Wintrob as CEO, effective Nov. 1.

Wintrob previously served as president and chief executive of AIG Life and Retirement, the U.S.-based life and retirement services businesses of American International Group <AIG.N>. In addition, Bruce Karsh, president and a co-founder of Oaktree, will join Howard Marks as co-chairman.